        <h1>Cheetah Facts</h1>
        <p>The cheetah is a large, slender cat that lives in sub-Saharan Africa. Here are some astonishing facts about cheetahs:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Cheetahs are the fastest land animals, reaching speeds of up to 98 kilometers per hour (61 miles per hour).</li>
            <li><strong>Appearance:</strong> They have a tan coat with black spots and tear-shaped streaks on their faces.</li>
            <li><strong>Diet:</strong> Cheetahs primarily hunt impalas, wildebeest calves, and gazelles.</li>
            <li><strong>Habitat:</strong> They inhabit dry grasslands, scrub forests, and savannahs.</li>
            <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> In the wild, cheetahs live between 10 and 15 years.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Learn more about these incredible creatures and their adaptations!</p>
